node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

The Senate's massive $1.2 trillion infrastructure package marked a big bipartisan achievement after months of negotiations. The new investments, which still needs to be passed by the House, would reach far beyond the traditional infrastructure projects for roads, bridges and railroads. Here are five things in the bill that might surprise you.

(📸: Shutterstock, Moriah Ratner/Bloomberg/Getty Images, Patrick T. Fallon/AFP/Getty Images and Chris McGrath/Getty Images)

Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of phone and text that says '1. Broadband upgrade The legislation would provide a $65 billion investment in improving the nation's broadband infrastructure. It aims to lower the price households pay for internet service by requiring federal funding recipients to offer low-cost affordable plans, by creating price transparency and by boosting competition in areas where existing providers aren't providing adequate service. CNN INFRASTRUCTURE BILL'.

Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'ZEROEMISSION MISSION 1EY A 20204 E282124 2. Electric school buses $5 billion would help school districts replace yellow school buses with clean, American-made, zero-emission buses. It would also invest $7.5 billion to build a nationwide network of plug-in electric vehicle chargers. CNN INFRASTRUCTURE BILL'.

Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '3. Address historic inequities The legislation contains $1 billion to reconnect communities, disproportionately Black neighborhoods, that were divided by highways and other infrastructure, according to the White House. It would fund planning, design, demolition and reconstruction of street grids, parks or other infrastructure. CNN INFRASTRUCTURE BILL'.

Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Swp TSI 4. New tax regulations on cryptocurrencies A provision tucked away at the end of the Senate bill would impose new tax reporting requirements on cryptocurrency transactions a move that congressional estimates say could raise $28 billion in new revenue to help pay for the infrastructure package. CNN INFRASTRUCTURE BILL'.

Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of text that says '5. Delaying a drug rebate rule To help pay for the infrastructure spending, the legislation would delay the implementation of a controversial Trump administration rule that would radically change how drugs are priced and paid for in Medicare and Medicaid. It's expected to save $51 billion. CNN INFRASTRUCTURE BILL'.

node.text: About 486,332 people are receiving their first Covid-19 vaccine dose each day in the US, which is a 10% increase over last week's pace and the highest daily average since June 18, according to data published Monday by the CDC. The improvements are promising, but just over half of the total population is fully vaccinated, and 31.2% of the vaccine-eligible population remains unvaccinated. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.

node.text:
A young boy in Las Vegas had a surprise waiting for him as he headed out for the first day of fourth grade on Monday — a police escort to honor his late father. Over the summer break, Noah, 9, mourned the death of his father, Officer Jason Swanger of the Las Vegas Metropolitan Police Department. Swanger, 41, died from Covid-19 complications in June, according to the police department. "He was known as a devoted father and husband who went the extra mile for people in need," according to the department's press release on Swanger's death. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.⁠
⁠
(📸: KTNV)

“The best way I can help now is if I step aside and let government get back to governing,” said New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo. He said his resignation would take effect in two weeks, when he will hand over the reins to his deputy, Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Kathy Hochul will replace Cuomo, becoming New York's first female governor CNN 2 12 BREAKING NEWS'.

node.text:
New York Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul will soon become the state's first female governor, replacing Gov. Andrew Cuomo. A Buffalo native, she was first elected lieutenant governor of New York in 2014 as Cuomo's running mate and won reelection alongside him in 2018.⁠
⁠
"I agree with Governor Cuomo's decision to step down. It is the right thing to do and in the best interest of New Yorkers," Hochul tweeted Tuesday shortly after Cuomo's announcement. In the wake of the state attorney general's report last week, she denounced Cuomo's alleged behavior as "repulsive & unlawful," adding, "I believe these brave women & admire their courage coming forward."⁠
⁠
(📸: Lev Radin/Sipa USA/AP)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Gov. Andrew Cuomo resigns in wake of investigation into sexual harassment allegations OF THE STATS SDAL OF GREAT NEW HHOX EXCELSIOR CNN BREAKING NEWS'.

node.text:
New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo has announced he is stepping aside from his office, effective in 14 days. A New York state investigation released last week found Cuomo “sexually harassed multiple women and violated state law.” Cuomo has repeatedly denied the allegations, but today said he has “been too familiar with people” and apologized to the women he said he “truly offended.” After the state report was released, President Biden, Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi and more than two thirds of New York state senators called on Cuomo to resign.⁠
⁠
(📸: Spencer Platt/Getty Images North America)

node.text:
The US Senate passed a historic, sweeping $1.2 trillion infrastructure package on Tuesday by a wide bipartisan majority vote of 69-30. The bill is now headed to the House of Representatives, where it faces an uncertain future before reaching President Biden’s desk. ⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio to read our breakdown of what's in the bill.

node.text:
Teenage climate activist Greta Thunberg is the cover star of Vogue Scandinavia's first issue. In an accompanying profile, Thunberg spotlighted the role of fast fashion — the mass production of inexpensive, on-trend clothing that maintains low pricing through labor exploitation and poor quality — in the worsening climate crisis. "If you are buying fast fashion then you are contributing to that industry and encouraging them to expand and encouraging them to continue their harmful process," she told the magazine. Tap the link in our bio to learn more. ⁠
⁠
(📸: Alexandrov Klum/Vogue Scandinavia)

node.text:
The pterosaur, with a nearly 30-foot wingspan, flew over Australia 105 million years ago, according to new findings published Monday in the Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology. Its spearlike mouth was perfect for plucking fish from the sea. "It's the closest thing we have to a real life dragon," said Tim Richards, the study's lead author.⁠
⁠
(📸: University of Queensland/Adobe Stock)

node.text: More than 99.99% of people who are fully vaccinated against Covid-19 have not had a breakthrough case resulting in hospitalization or death, according to a CNN analysis of data from the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. As of August 2, more than 164 million people in the United States were fully vaccinated against Covid-19, according to the CDC. Fewer than 0.001% of vaccinated people — 1,507 people — have died and fewer than 0.005% — 7,101 people — have been hospitalized with Covid-19.⁠
